My husband was a two tour helicopter pilot in Vietnam, 1967-1968 and 1970-1971. He sprayed agent orange for over a three month period on his first trip and was sxposed to it again while flying Cobras on his second tour. In the early 80's he took a AO exam at the Gainesville VA and the areas where he flew matched the areas on the map overlays that they had. He has flight records that show the dates he sprayed. He even got a small settlement from the class action suit that was filed back in the early 90's. It's funny that a famous insurance agency would pay compensation,when we all know that they seldom pay unless there is substantiual proof.<br><br>
He has been treated for high blood preasure since his discharge in 1972. but over the years has also suffered from skin rashes, diebetes, leasions on his hands and feet that brake open and bleed. He has 5 different skin conditions, PTSD,pancretitis, neuropithy in his hands and feet,(of coourse the VA says this is from the diebetes.),he has problems with his memory, sometimes he can't even finish a sentance because he forgets what he is saying. he can't sleep more than an hour at a time and often suffers from &quot;flashbacks&quot;. If there is anyone out there that can help us get the military to WAKE UP, please contact us. <br><br>
Thank You.<br>
PS his total disability from the military is only 30%.<br>

